=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Tutorials_08-Scoping-and-Plotting_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 221 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 220.6358
  harmonic_decay_rate: -5.6099
  harmonic_regularity: 0.2141
  pitch_clarity: 96.6248
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -11.2456
  resonance_freq: 516.7969

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: 08. Scoping and Plotting Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Tutorials/Getting-Started/08-Scoping-and-Plotting.html
